  <pbcoreTitle titleType='Program'>After the murder of four children / James Baldwin.</pbcoreTitle>
  <pbcoreSubject>16th Street Baptist Church Bombing, Birmingham, Ala., 1963</pbcoreSubject>
  <pbcoreSubject>Terrorism -- United States</pbcoreSubject>
  <pbcoreSubject>African Americans--Civil rights--History</pbcoreSubject>
  <pbcoreDescription>
     After the bombing of the 16th Street Baptist Church in Birmingham, Alabama
    on September 15, 1963, James Baldwin spoke to an overflowing crowd at the
    New York Community Church. Baldwin spoke against the use of terrorism to
    achieve political aims. The speech was recorded by WBAI at the New York
    Community Church, 25 September 1963. 
  </pbcoreDescription>
